message.content: cs.AR, cs.AR because the paper proposes a new DRAM substrate that enables fast and efficient data movement across a large range of memory at low cost, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR). Other possible sub-categories could include cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.ET (embedded systems), as the paper discusses the potential applications of LISA in improving system performance and energy efficiency. However, cs.AR is the most likely sub-category as it directly relates to the proposed DRAM substrate.
